\fs102 \cf4 How to Make Block Themes Better with Theme JSON\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf5 Last Updated May 28, 2025 12 minute read
\fs40 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
Key points:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
WordPress theme settings were previously scattered across files, but are now mostly held within the theme.json file.\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Its structure covers a wide range of settings, including the schema, version, custom templates, and patterns.\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
You can modify theme.json directly with code for advanced control or visually through the Site Editor for visual customization.\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Theme.json integrates with block development frameworks like ACF Blocks, allowing custom blocks to inherit your theme\'92s global style system.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\partightenfactor0
\cf2 For years, WordPress theme settings were scattered \'96 defined in functions.php, buried in PHP hooks, or hardcoded into stylesheets. It worked, but barely. Now, there\'92s theme.json \'96 a single, declarative file that brings order to the chaos. It centralizes theme configuration and design tokens, letting developers define global settings like colors, typography, layout, and spacing in one place.\
The real payoff is in the block editor: theme.json powers the Global Styles interface, so designers can tweak visual styles directly \'96 without risking layout breakage. Developers, meanwhile, keep control over what can and can\'92t be changed. The output is lean: only the CSS you specify, with no bloat and fewer fights over selector priority.\
More than just a convenience, theme.json is now the standard foundation of all core themes. It\'92s tightly integrated with the WordPress editor and aligned with where the platform is headed.\
Let\'92s explore how it works and why it\'92s fundamental for modern WordPress development.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
