\fs52 \cf4 Custom templates\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 The customTemplates key lets you register additional page templates that appear in the Template dropdown within the editor. These are useful for offering alternate layouts \'96 like a no-header landing page \'96 without requiring users to touch code.\
Each template entry is an object with three fields:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\fs28 \cf7 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf7 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"name" 
\f0\fs32 \cf2 matches the filename (e.g., templates/landing-no-header.html in a block theme or page-landing-no-header.php in a classic theme).\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\fs28 \cf7 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf7 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"title"
\f0\fs32 \cf2  is the human-readable name shown in the editor.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\fs28 \cf7 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf7 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"postTypes"
\f0\fs32 \cf2  defines where the template is available, usually 
\f1\fs28 \cf7 ["page"]
\f0\fs32 \cf2 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Take the code sample below:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

